message.content:
cs.SC, cs.CG, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper proposes adaptations of regular chains and triangular decompositions, which are fundamental tools in symbolic computation, for semi-algebraic systems. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as triangular decompositions are commonly used in computational geometry to partition a space into simpler regions. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as semi-algebraic systems are a topic in mathematical logic and the paper proposes algorithms for decomposing them. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as semi-algebraic systems are used in control theory and the paper proposes a method for decomposing them.
